I would think this should be defined first as a functor from the category of simplicial sets, and secondly from topological spaces. Also, it would be nice to have a more general definition for the "coefficients". At the very least, the chain complex with coefficient `M` should be defined for any `M : ModuleCat R` (and not only for `R` itself).
One approach would be to take a preadditive "coefficient category `C`" and an object `M : C`, and consider the extension to simplicial objects of the functor which sends a type `A` to the coproduct of copies of `M` indexed by `A` (assuming `C` has coproducts of size `u` for a certain universe `u`).
It would be reasonable to move this to `AlgebraicTopology.SingularHomology.Basic`.
